Roughly speaking, the __spectral curve__ is a locus of zeros of the characteristic polynomial of the [[Lax pair|Lax matrix]] of a classical [[integrable system]]. Hitchin has taken a deeper geometric point of view in terms of moduli space of [[stable vector bundles]] of fixed rank $r$ and degree $d$ over a fixed projective nonsingular curve $\Sigma$ of genus $g$. A point in the cotangent space of this bundle is a stable vector bundle equipped with a 1-form valued endomorphism; to each such datum one associates a spectral curve. 

